In medium saucepan, bring 2 cups water, rice-bean mix, Special Seasonings, 1 tablespoon margarine and bell pepper to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Meanwhile, sprinkle fish with Creole seasoning. In large skillet over medium-high heat, heat remaining 1 tablespoon margarine and oil until hot. Add fish; cook 4 minutes. Turn fish over; reduce heat to medium-low. Cook 6 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve fish and chopped tomato over beans and rice. Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.